Commentary: SIX! Oh, that would have been one of the catches of the entire year but Chris Woakes was just a millisecond or so early and it will be a six. Tossed up on middle, Salman Agha steps out and looks to go straight down the ground but ends up slicing up high and towards the long off fence. Woakes there backtracks and completes the catch but his momentum is taking him over. He lobs the ball back up, does a 360 over the ropes and then leaps back up to complete the catch. However, the replays from behind the fence show that his right leg was just in contact with the ground when he made contact with the ball again and Salman will be a relieved man.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, England have bowled out Pakistan after 149 overs. Root flattens the trajectory and quickens the pace of the ball, and angles it across the batter like a bumper. Abrar Ahmed is hurried into the shot as he arches back and looks to guide it down to deep third but it bounces a bit more. Abrar is late to slash it and it goes off the higher part and straight to Ben Duckett at the first slip who is quick to react and takes a very sharp catch by stretching his hands in the direction of the ball. Duckett though immediately signals to the dressing room and looks in huge discomfort. He probably has dislocated his left thumb. Pakistan end their first innings on 556.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! PLUCKED FROM THIN AIR! ABSOLUTE SCREAMER! Pakistan wouldn't have expected for a better start than this! Naseem Shah bowls it on a hard length, slightly nipping into the batter from middle, Ollie Pope positions himself on the back foot and pulls it flat in an attempt to get it past mid-wicket. He hits it hard and in the air towards the right of mid-wicket where Aamer Jamal dives to the direction of the ball and takes a wonderful one-handed catch in the air to dismiss the English skipper. Commentary: OUT! PLUMB IN FRONT! The bowling change works straight away for Pakistan. End of a marathon knock from Joe Root. Nice to see every single Pakistani player walk up to Root to congratulate him as he trudges off. This is pushed through by Agha, on a nagging length, on off, a hint of turn towards the batter. Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR AND MAGNIFICENTLY TAKEN BY DUCKETT! The demons have returned to haunt Pakistan in the second innings, but this was an ordinary shot from Saim Ayub especially when they lost Babar on the very previous delivery. Around the wicket charges Brydon Carse, hits the short of a length outside off. Ayub looks to flat bat this over covers but gets nowhere from the sweet spot of the bat and he loses his shape a bit as well. As a result, it goes high in the air over mid off. Ben Duckett turns around from mid off, locks his eyes on the ball, and takes a good sliding catch over his right shoulder. Saim Ayub goes for 25 (35), which seemed like a brain-freeze moment for him. Brydon Carse gets his first wicket and Pakistan are 41/4 now.

Commentary: OUT! THROUGH HIS DEFENCE! BOWLED'EM! A seed of a delivery by Carse and half of the Pakistani side is back in the sheds now. This is an astonishing collapse for Pakistan. Over the wickets, a wobbled-seam delivery by Carse, on a touch fuller length, lands right on the crack and jags back in very sharply cutting the right-hander into half. Mohammad Rizwan is cramped up for room and trapped in front, stays rooted in the crease and is clueless to negotiate it. By the time he could bring the bat down in time, the ball zips through his defence and clatters the middle stump. Mohammad Rizwan departs on 10 (19) with a grim look on his face. Pakistan are 59/5 and trail by 208 more runs, and are quite possible staring down an inning defeat here.

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Leach comes and provides that breakthrough for England they were looking for! Salman Agha has straightaway reviewed it though, but even the umpire's call cannot save him on this one. This is an in-drifter from Leach, the one that straightens up off the deck, pitched full and on middle and leg, Salman Agha leans on the front foot to defend and anticipates the ball to turn and plays for the spin. Instead, it goes straight on and Agha plays all over the line. UltraEdge shows no bat involved and the Ball Tracking comes up with three reds as the ball clips the leg stump on the projection. Pakistan burn a review but more importantly, they have lost a well-set batter in the form of Salman Agha. And the bowling change has worked wonders for England as they now are just a couple of wickets away from a win. Leach breaks the 109-run stand for the 7th wicket.

Commentary: DROPPED! 5TH CATCH PUT DOWN BY ENGLAND! The culprit is the English skipper now, Ollie Pope! Although, this was a very tough chance. Should've been taken whatsoever at this level. Aamer Jamal has been dropped twice now. First on 12 and now on 50. Banged into the surface, climbs on the batter as it skids through quickly, Aamer Jamal is late to react on the pull but goes through the shot and slices it over the square leg region. Ollie Pope from the inner ring, backtracks it and slides on to catch. Gets his hands on the ball at the shoulder level but drops it eventually as the ball pops out of his palms. Allows a single. Brydon Carse can be seen with a muted disappointment on his face.
